headline: Bitcoin profits, Expedia, Thanksgiving market gains: Market Minute
summary: Yahoo Finance host Rachelle Akuffo breaks down several of this morning's top market stories and trending stocks. Bitcoin (BTC-USD) holders made a record $2.2 billion in daily realized profits as the cryptocurrency returns to its march back to $100,000. Baird analysts initiated coverage on Expedia Group (EXPE) with an Outperform rating. With Thanksgiving just one day away, the S&P 500 (^GSPC) has historically seen significant gains in the shortened trading week. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Wealth here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.

headline: Baird starts Expedia and Booking with ‘outperform’ amid strong travel demand
summary: Investing.com -- Baird on Wednesday said it was initiating coverage on online booking firms Expedia Inc (NASDAQ:EXPE) and Booking Holdings Inc (NASDAQ:BKNG), giving them both an “outperform” rating, citing positive travel demand environment.

headline: Expedia (EXPE) Post Q3 Earnings: Buy, Sell, or Hold?
summary: What a time it’s been for Expedia. In the past six months alone, the company’s stock price has increased by a massive 69.5%, reaching $186.59 per share. This performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
